{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RRPzXw9Ekgu1zf3ZyjhSZT","type":"tool_result","content":"   440→```\n   441→[FAIL] verify-env build failed: {error}\n   442→```\n   443→Leave story at `verifying`, go to Step 6. No fallback.\n   444→\n   445→**3d-ii: Start Docker container**\n   446→\n   447→```bash\n   448→docker run -d --name codeharness-verify --network host \\\n   449→  -e ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=\"$ANTHROPIC_API_KEY\" \\\n   450→  codeharness-verify sleep infinity\n   451→```\n   452→\n   453→`--network host` allows the container to reach OTEL Collector at `localhost:4318`, VictoriaLogs at `:9428`, VictoriaMetrics at `:8428`, and VictoriaTraces at `:16686`. The `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` env var enables the `claude` CLI inside the container for verifier sessions that need to spawn Claude subprocesses.\n   454→\n   455→If `docker run` fails, log `[FAIL] docker run failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to Step 6. No cleanup needed — the container never started.\n   456→\n   457→**3d-iii: Prepare clean workspace**\n   458→\n   459→```bash\n   460→codeharness verify-env prepare --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   461→```\n   462→\n   463→This creates `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}` with built artifacts, docs, and story file — but NO source code.\n   464→\n   465→If this fails, log `[FAIL] verify-env prepare failed: {error}`, leave story at `verifying`, and go to cleanup (step 3d-viii) then Step 6. The container is running and must be cleaned up.\n   466→\n   467→**3d-iv: Run verifier session**\n   468→\n   469→Build the verification prompt and spawn the verifier:\n   470→\n   471→1. Read the story content from `/tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/story.md`\n   472→2. Read the prompt template from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts` — use `verifyPromptTemplate()` with the story content, container name `codeharness-verify`, and default observability endpoints\n   473→3. Run the verifier:\n   474→\n   475→```bash\n   476→cd /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key} && claude --print --max-budget-usd 5 --allowedTools Bash Read Write Glob Grep Edit -p \"{verification_prompt}\"\n   477→```\n   478→\n   479→The prompt (from `src/templates/verify-prompt.ts`) instructs the verifier that:\n   480→\n   481→- It has **NO source code access** — `src/` does not exist in the workspace\n   482→- **ALL CLI commands** must run via `docker exec codeharness-verify <command>`\n   483→- It should read `README.md` for usage guidance\n   484→- It should query observability endpoints from the host:\n   485→  - VictoriaLogs: `http://localhost:9428`\n   486→  - VictoriaMetrics: `http://localhost:8428`\n   487→  - VictoriaTraces: `http://localhost:16686`\n   488→- The proof document goes in `verification/{story_key}-proof.md` within the clean workspace\n   489→- REAL failures must be reported — never fabricate evidence\n   490→- ACs that cannot be verified should be marked `[ESCALATE]`\n   491→\n   492→If the verifier process exits non-zero or times out, treat as failure (proceed to retry logic in step 3d-vii).\n   493→\n   494→**3d-v: Copy proof document back**\n   495→\n   496→```bash\n   497→cp /tmp/codeharness-verify-{story_key}/verification/{story_key}-proof.md verification/\n   498→```\n   499→\n   500→If the proof file does not exist (verifier crashed or failed to produce one), treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   501→\n   502→**3d-vi: Validate proof quality**\n   503→\n   504→```bash\n   505→codeharness verify --story {story_key} 2>&1\n   506→```\n   507→\n   508→Parse the output/exit code. After parsing each AC verdict from the proof, update the live progress:\n   509→\n   510→```bash\n   511→codeharness progress --ac-progress \"{passed}/{total}\"\n   512→```\n   513→\n   514→where `passed` is ACs with PASS verdict and `total` is all ACs.\n   515→\n   516→- If `pending === 0` and `escalated === 0` → proof quality passed. Update sprint-status.yaml: change `{story_key}` status to `done`. Print: `[OK] Story {story_key}: verifying → done`. Proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   517→- If `escalated > 0` and `pending === 0` → verifier could not reach some ACs. **Before accepting escalation, diagnose WHY:**\n   518→  1. Read the proof document. For each `[ESCALATE]` AC, check the reason.\n   519→  2. **If the reason is infrastructure/tooling** (container missing binary, tree-shaking, Docker not configured, wrong version installed): this is NOT a valid escalation. The infrastructure needs fixing. Treat as **Path C** below.\n   520→  3. **If the reason is genuinely impossible to automate** (requires physical hardware, paid external service, human visual judgment): accept the escalation. Print: `[WARN] Story {story_key} has {N} genuinely escalated ACs — marking done with known limitations`. Update status to `done`.\n   521→  4. **Do NOT leave stories at `verifying` with escalated ACs.** Either fix the infra problem (Path C) or accept and mark done.\n   522→- If `pending > 0` → proof has gaps. Treat as failure (step 3d-vii).\n   523→\n   524→If the verifier made code fixes (detected by checking `git diff` after verification), run:\n   525→```bash\n   526→npm run build && npm run test:unit\n   527→```\n   528→to confirm fixes haven't broken anything. Then proceed to cleanup (step 3d-viii).\n   529→\n   530→**3d-vii: Failure handling — code bugs vs infrastructure failures**\n   531→\n   532→Determine the failure type. There are two distinct paths:\n   533→\n   534→**Path A — Code bugs (`pending > 0` in proof validation):**\n   535→\n   536→A proof document exists and `codeharness verify` reported `pending > 0`. This means the feature has real bugs — the code does not satisfy the ACs. Code bugs NEVER count against the retry budget.\n   537→\n   538→1. **Extract failing ACs from the proof document.** Read `verification/{story_key}-proof.md`. For each AC section (`## AC N: description`), check if the verdict is not PASS and not `[ESCALATE]`. For each failing AC, extract:\n   539→   - The AC number and description (from the `## AC N:` heading)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PmuW6xAsA3LVJUCbfjE8R9","session_id":"caf97759-8abf-4687-a81a-d927d13354ea","uuid":"4221c6a1-847a-4fbc-aa02-56615613e37c","timestamp":"2026-03-27T12:56:45.228Z"}
