{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01NGxZTbjacf6dBCjgenVT4r","type":"tool_result","content":"   810→   - Verification gaps (escalated ACs, weak evidence)\n   811→   - Tooling/infrastructure problems (sandbox, permissions, CLI issues)\n   812→3. **Cost analysis** — from the cost report:\n   813→   - Total API-equivalent cost this sprint\n   814→   - Cost per phase (which phases are most expensive?)\n   815→   - Cost per story (which stories cost the most and why?)\n   816→   - Wasted spend (no-op sessions, failed verifications, retries)\n   817→   - Cost optimization opportunities:\n   818→     * Stories that should use unit-testable verification instead of Docker\n   819→     * Phases that could be cheaper (e.g., lighter retros for no-op sessions)\n   820→     * Subagent prompts that could be trimmed to reduce cache writes\n   821→     * Average cost per story vs target (flag if trending up)\n   822→4. **What went well** — stories completed, bugs fixed, process improvements\n   823→5. **What went wrong** — failures, blockers, stuck stories, wasted iterations\n   824→6. **Lessons learned** — patterns to repeat or avoid\n   825→7. **Action items** — concrete next steps, split into:\n   826→   - Fix now (before next session)\n   827→   - Fix soon (next sprint)\n   828→   - Backlog (track but not urgent)\n   829→   - Cost optimization (specific actions to reduce token consumption)\n   830→\n   831→Write the retrospective to _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/session-retro-{date}.md where {date} is today's date in YYYY-MM-DD format.\n   832→\n   833→If a session retro for today already exists, append to it with a `---` separator and timestamp.\n   834→\n   835→Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously.\n   836→Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\"\n   837→  subagent_type: \"general-purpose\"\n   838→```\n   839→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01PmuW6xAsA3LVJUCbfjE8R9","sessi