 the ordering makes some sense since escalate delegates TO the other sections and environment-provable is the longest section.\n\n### Review Outcome\n\n- All HIGH and MEDIUM issues fixed\n- Coverage: 96.86% overall (target: 90%), all 158 files above 80% floor\n- Build passes, 3959/3959 tests pass\n- Story status updated to `verifying`\n\n### Files Modified\n\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/commands/harness-run.md` — fixed stale \"black-box\" and \"unit-testable\" terminology\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/parser.ts` — added `black-box` to `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN`\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/verify/__tests__/verify-parser.test.ts` — added test for `black-box` → `environment-provable` mapping\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md` — status → `verifying`\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **MEDIUM (fixed)**: Stale \"black-box verification\" text in failure template at `commands/harness-run.md:548`\n- **MEDIUM (fixed)**: Stale \"unit-testable verification\" text in retrospective prompt at `commands/harness-run.md:818`\n- **MEDIUM (fixed)**: `VERIFICATION_TAG_PATTERN` regex in `parser.ts` missing `black-box` value — legacy mapping was documented but non-functional\n- **LOW (not fixed)**: Section ordering mismatch between routing table and actual sections in harness-run.md. Cosmetic, tests depend on current order.\n- **LOW (not fixed)**: All 34 dispatch tests are string-matching against markdown content — inherently brittle. Any wording change in harness-run.md will break them. This is acceptable for prompt-file testing but is tech debt.\n- **Coverage gaps**: No integration tests for the actual dispatch routing at runtime (the tests verify the markdown contains the right strings, not that an LLM agent would correctly follow the instructions). This is the nature of prompt engineering — no automated way to test LLM co