{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01ESkRbZWrLEKYL9pvRCDL8F","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 16.5: Rewrite harness-run Verification Dispatch\n     2→<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n     3→\n     4→Status: verifying\n     5→\n     6→<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n     7→\n     8→## Story\n     9→\n    10→As a codeharness developer,\n    11→I want the harness-run Step 3d verification dispatch to use four-tier routing instead of binary unit-testable/black-box,\n    12→So that each verification tier gets the appropriate verification strategy (build+test, local run, Docker stack, or escalation).\n    13→\n    14→## Acceptance Criteria\n    15→\n    16→- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3d-0, when a story file is read, then the verification tier is derived by parsing ALL AC-level `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags and computing `maxTier()` across them — the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is NOT used for dispatch <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    17→- [ ] AC2: Given a story where all ACs are tagged `test-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then verification runs via a single subagent that builds, runs tests, and inspects code — no Docker, no running the app <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    18→- [ ] AC3: Given a story where the derived tier is `runtime-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then a subagent builds the artifact, runs it locally (e.g., `npm start`, `cargo run`), interacts with it, and checks behavior — no Docker stack needed <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    19→- [ ] AC4: Given a story where the derived tier is `environment-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then the existing full Docker verification flow runs (`codeharness stack start`, docker exec, observability checks) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    20→- [ ] AC5: Given a story where the derived tier is `escalate`, when Step 3d dispatches, then escalated ACs are marked `[ESCALATE]` and non-escalated ACs are verified at their individual tier levels <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    21→- [ ] AC6: Given a story file with the old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` story-level tag, when Step 3d reads it, then the story-level tag is ignored and AC-level tier derivation is used instead (backward compat: old stories still work because their AC tags are parsed) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    22→- [ ] AC7: Given Step 3d-0 encounters ACs with legacy tags like `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->`, when tier derivation runs, then `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to new tiers before computing `maxTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n    23→\n    24→## Tasks / Subtasks\n    25→\n    26→- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Step 3d-0 in `commands/harness-run.md` (AC: 1, 6, 7)\n    27→  - [x] 1.1: Replace the binary `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag check (L261-L267) with AC-level tier derivation instructions\n    28→  - [x] 1.2: Add instructions: parse all AC lines for `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags, map legacy values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, compute `maxTier()`. Default to `test-provable` if no tags found\n    29→  - [x] 1.3: Add note: the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is ignored; AC-level tags are the source of truth\n    30→- [x] Task 2: Rewrite the test-provable dispatch section (AC: 2)"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"caf97759-8abf-4687-a81a-d927d13354ea","uuid":"f17ec6ca-b28f-42c3-a3e2-095bd0509b20","timestamp":"2026-03-27T13:02:17.174Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-5-rewrite-harness-run-verification-dispatch.md","content":"# Story 16.5: Rewrite harness-run Verification Dispatch\n<!-- verification-tier: test-provable -->\n\nStatus: verifying\n\n<!-- Note: Validation is optional. Run validate-create-story for quality check before dev-story. -->\n\n## Story\n\nAs a codeharness developer,\nI want the harness-run Step 3d verification dispatch to use four-tier routing instead of binary unit-testable/black-box,\nSo that each verification tier gets the appropriate verification strategy (build+test, local run, Docker stack, or escalation).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n- [ ] AC1: Given harness-run Step 3d-0, when a story file is read, then the verification tier is derived by parsing ALL AC-level `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags and computing `maxTier()` across them — the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is NOT used for dispatch <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC2: Given a story where all ACs are tagged `test-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then verification runs via a single subagent that builds, runs tests, and inspects code — no Docker, no running the app <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC3: Given a story where the derived tier is `runtime-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then a subagent builds the artifact, runs it locally (e.g., `npm start`, `cargo run`), interacts with it, and checks behavior — no Docker stack needed <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC4: Given a story where the derived tier is `environment-provable`, when Step 3d dispatches, then the existing full Docker verification flow runs (`codeharness stack start`, docker exec, observability checks) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC5: Given a story where the derived tier is `escalate`, when Step 3d dispatches, then escalated ACs are marked `[ESCALATE]` and non-escalated ACs are verified at their individual tier levels <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC6: Given a story file with the old `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` story-level tag, when Step 3d reads it, then the story-level tag is ignored and AC-level tier derivation is used instead (backward compat: old stories still work because their AC tags are parsed) <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n- [ ] AC7: Given Step 3d-0 encounters ACs with legacy tags like `<!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->` or `<!-- verification: integration-required -->`, when tier derivation runs, then `LEGACY_TIER_MAP` maps them to new tiers before computing `maxTier()` <!-- verification: test-provable -->\n\n## Tasks / Subtasks\n\n- [x] Task 1: Rewrite Step 3d-0 in `commands/harness-run.md` (AC: 1, 6, 7)\n  - [x] 1.1: Replace the binary `<!-- verification-tier: unit-testable -->` tag check (L261-L267) with AC-level tier derivation instructions\n  - [x] 1.2: Add instructions: parse all AC lines for `<!-- verification: {tier} -->` tags, map legacy values via `LEGACY_TIER_MAP`, compute `maxTier()`. Default to `test-provable` if no tags found\n  - [x] 1.3: Add note: the story-level `<!-- verification-tier: -->` tag is ignored; AC-level tags are the source of truth\n- [x] Task 2: Rewrite the test-provable dispatch section (AC: 2)","numLines":30,"startLine":1,"totalLines":130}}}
