{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_0146yq6YWwgg6oBSrYVHX5Wj","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n**Review Summary**\n\nStory 16-6 modifies two BMAD workflow files (excluded from code review per policy) and adds one test file. The implementation is correct — all ACs are satisfied. I found and fixed 3 issues in the test file:\n\n1. **HIGH**: AC8 test missing `distributed system` criterion (AC8 explicitly requires it). Fixed by adding to `it.each`.\n2. **MEDIUM**: AC1 test didn't verify VERIFICATION TIER TAGGING is within Step 5. Fixed by scoping assertion to `<step n=\"5\">`.\n3. **MEDIUM**: No test for \"Default to test-provable when unsure\" in instructions.xml (only in harness-run.md). Fixed by adding a test in AC2.\n\n**Coverage results**: 96.86% overall (target: 90%), all 158 files above 80% per-file floor.\n\n**Tests**: 151 files, 3961 tests, all pass. Zero regressions.\n\n**Story status**: Updated to `verifying`.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n**Bugs found:**\n- HIGH: AC8 test missing `distributed system` criterion — test would pass even if this keyword was removed from instructions.xml. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: AC1 test used global search instead of scoping to Step 5 — tier tagging block could be in any step and test would pass. Fixed.\n- MEDIUM: \"Default to test-provable when unsure\" instruction in instructions.xml had no test coverage (only harness-run.md was tested). Fixed.\n\n**Code quality issues found but NOT fixed (LOW):**\n- AC6-AC9 tests use `tierSection()` (broader scope) instead of `decisionTreeOnly()` — works because criteria keywords don't overlap with example text, but is less precise than the AC wording suggests\n- `extractSection` helper is called repeatedly per test (once per `it.each` iteration) — could cache results for minor performance gain\n- Test file reads workflow XML and markdown files using hardcoded relative paths with `../../../../` — fragile if test location changes\n\n**Coverage gaps:**\n- No test verifies the `&lt;!--` XML escaping is correctly used for ALL example tags (only checks that `verification: {tier}` strings appear, not that they're properly XML-escaped in all 4 examples)\n- No negative test: what if someone adds a 5th invalid tier to the decision tree? Tests only check presence, not exclusivity.\n\n**Architecture concerns:**\n- None. This is a content-verification test for workflow files — appropriate pattern.\n\n**Items sent back for re-development:**\n- None. All HIGH and MEDIUM issues were fixed in this session.\n\n## Token Report\n\n- Total tool calls: 18\n- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 5, Edit: 3, Grep: 3, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n- Largest Bash outputs (top 3 by line count): full test suite run (~30 lines visible), initial test run (~10 lines), git show stat (~12 lines)\n- Files read: 7 unique, 8 total read calls (no file read 3+ times)\n- Redundant operations: none significant — one re-read of the test file after understanding the story was necessary for the edit cycle"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a1fe693be49c67e00 (use SendMessage with to: 'a1fe693be49c67e00' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 54522\ntool_uses: 31\nduration_ms: 256903</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"caf97759-8abf-4687-a81a-d927d13354ea","uuid":"e6f0493d-9307-421d-8ecc-888cd2a43d33","timestamp":"2026-03-27T13:10:11.451Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Run /bmad-code-review for the story at _bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/16-6-update-create-story-tier-criteria.md — perform adversarial review, fix all HIGH and MEDIUM issues found. After fixing, run `codeharness coverage --min-file 80` and ensure all files pass the per-file floor and the overall 90% target. Update the story status to `verifying` when all issues are fixed and coverage passes. Do NOT ask the user any questions — proceed autonomously. Do NOT run git commit. Do NOT run git add. Do NOT modify sprint-status.yaml.\n\nMANDATORY — End your response