eview` despite commits confirming them as done. Proof documents existed. Fixed by restoring `done` status. Root cause: likely ralph state reconciliation overwriting committed state between sessions.\n    44→\n    45→### 14-4-observability-backend-choice — verify (2026-03-27T08:20Z)\n    46→\n    47→Tier A validation — proof existed with 10/10 PASS. Quick validation pass.\n    48→\n    49→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — review (2026-03-27T08:25Z)\n    50→\n    51→**Bugs found:**\n    52→- HIGH: Unsafe `as StackName` type cast in `dockerfile-generator.ts` masking type safety — FIXED\n    53→- MEDIUM: Double `apt-get update` layer in Rust+Bevy Dockerfile output — FIXED\n    54→- MEDIUM: Unquoted Python dist filename in COPY instruction (`env.ts:162`) — NOT FIXED\n    55→\n    56→**Tech debt:**\n    57→- 14 stale `mockDetectStack` call sites in `verify-env.test.ts`\n    58→- No logging when `getStackProvider()` returns undefined\n    59→\n    60→## Token Report\n    61→- Total tool calls: 20\n    62→- By tool: Bash: 7, Read: 10, Edit: 3, Grep: 5, Glob: 1, Skill: 1\n    63→- Files read: 13 unique, 14 total reads\n    64→\n    65→### 14-5-stack-aware-verify-dockerfile — code-review (2026-03-27T09:35Z)\n    66→\n    67→**Bugs found and fixed:**\n    68→- HIGH: Subdirectory stack path not resolved before passing to provider — Bevy detection would silently fail for non-root stacks\n    69→- MEDIUM: Missing DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive — apt installs could hang on interactive prompts\n    70→- MEDIUM: Uncovered !provider and !section branches (66.66% branch coverage before fix)\n    71→- MEDIUM: env.ts at 305 lines (extra blank line), over NFR1 300-line limit\n    72→\n    73→**Code quality issues NOT fixed (LOW):**\n    74→- verify-env.test.ts still mocks dead detectStack import\n    75→- Multi-stack Dockerfile creates redundant apt-get update per provider section\n    76→- env.ts at 304 lines still over 300-line NFR1 limit\n    77→- Story Dev Agent Record claims 